akas: Regular Show in Space USA (eighth season title)
akas from release info: Regular Show in Space USA (eighth season title)

1.title: One Space Day at a Time
1.plot: Mortdecai and Rogby are doing their job and stumble upon a jewel that might change their lives.

2.title: Cool Bro Bots
2.plot: A group of robots come to help the guys in the dome

3.title: Welcome to Space
3.plot: The guys get rescued, but Benson desperately wants to get back

4.title: Space Creds
4.plot: While Mordecai and Rigby decide what movie to watch they see an ad and want these really cool rocket shoes so they need cress so it's there mission to find a job to get some.

5.title: Lost and Found
5.plot: The guys need to retrieve a wallet on a hostile planet

6.title: Ugly Moons
6.plot: Lost and Found: Mordecai and Rigby go get a wallet. / Ugly Moons: Muscle Man vows to prank someone.

7.title: The Dream Warrior
7.plot: The Dream Warrior: The guys help Pops overcome his nightmares. / The Brain of Evil: Mordecai and Rigby have to recapture something they lost.

8.title: The Brain of Evil
8.plot: Mordecai and Rigby need to catch a brain before it causes too much damage

9.title: Fries Night
9.plot: When Benson is dumped by his girlfriend Pam, he goes on a quest for French Fries to fill the void left in his Heart.

10.title: Spacey Mc SpaceTree
10.plot: Rigby must past a safety test.

11.title: Can You Ear Me Now?
11.plot: Mordecai and Rigby have to defend their case on a planet inhabited by ear people

12.title: Stuck in an Elevator
12.plot: Can You Ear Me Now?: Mordecai and Rigby offend some people. / Stuck in An Elevator: Mordecai and Rigby want to go to a reunion concert.

14.title: Operation: Hear No Evil
14.plot: The Space Race: The guys race in space. / Operation: Hear No Evil: Mordecai and Rigby want to avoid spoilers of their favorite TV show.

15.title: Space Escape
15.plot: The guys must escape a bad guy.

16.title: New Beds
16.plot: Space Escape: The guys have to escape from someone bad. / New Beds: The guys get new beds.

17.title: Mordeby and Rigbecai
17.plot: The two guys accidentally enter a teleport machine together, the results need to be reversed before it's too late

18.title: Alpha Dome
18.plot: Mordeby and Rigbecai: Mordecai and Rigby mess around with a teleportation machine, and you can pretty much imagine how this one goes. / Alpha Dome: The guys confront some people.

19.title: Terror Tales of the Park VI
19.plot: In Regular Show's sixth installment of "Terror Tales," the guys gather in the house on the Dome and tell scary Halloween stories just like ol' times, only this Halloween, the stories have an extra terrifying, science fiction twist.

20.title: The Ice Tape
20.plot: Pops finds a tape that contain answers to his questions

21.title: The Key to the Universe
21.plot: The Ice Tape: The guys need to play a very special VHS tape. / The Key To The Universe: The guys learn something super important.

23.title: Christmas in Space
23.plot: The guys celebrate their first Christmas in space by opening presents, eating peppermint bark and telling Christmas stories. Benson wants the stories to be more Christmas-y, but the guys keep adding scary elements, which only infuriate their boss.

24.title: Kill 'Em with Kindness
24.plot: Pops still doesn't wish to fight Anti-Pops and wants to peacefully work things out, but everyone else doubts kindness will stop Anti-Pops.

25.title: Meet the Seer
25.plot: After the incident between Pops and Anti-Pops, the gang search out to find the Seer.

26.title: Cheer Up Pops
26.plot: The gang try to support Pops for the imminent battle against Anti-Pops

27.title: A Regular Epic Final Battle
27.plot: In the series finale, Mordecai, Rigby and the park workers aids pops in an epic final battle against Anti-pops on Lollipop world and to save the universe, that's right, the universe!

0.title: The Pilot
0.plot: Mordecai the blue jay and Rigby the raccoon play paper rock scissors for a chair, but they get into a 100 times tie.

1.title: The Power
1.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby need a raise to fix a hole in their bedroom wall, they use a magical keyboard that allows them to do anything they want.

2.title: Just Set Up the Chairs
2.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to prove to Benson that they are not "slackers" by actually completing a job given to them, setting up the chairs for a kid's birthday party.

3.title: Caffeinated Coffee Tickets
3.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try work overtime to earn enough money to buy tickets to a Fist Pump concert, but when they run out of coffee to keep them awake, they enlist the help of a business man and a coffee-bean to keep the coffee flowing.

4.title: Death Punchies
4.plot: When Rigby becomes tired of losing at "punchies", he visits Death Kwon Do, a mediocre martial-arts clinic, to learn a move that will enable him to win.

5.title: Free Cake
5.plot: Mordecai and Rigby find a plate that they think would look good with cake, but when they don't have enough money for any, they use Skips' upcoming birthday as an excuse to throw a party and to eat the chocolate cake at the snack bar.

6.title: Meat Your Maker
6.plot: Mordecai and Rigby have to look for hot dogs in the meat locker when they burn the ones that Benson bought, but Rigby's incompetence ends up getting them locked in.

7.title: Grilled Cheese Deluxe
7.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby eat Benson's grilled cheese sandwich, Benson makes them buy another one. Unaware that it was Benson's sandwich because of Rigby's lie, Mordecai makes a bet to see who can lie the most without getting caught.

8.title: The Unicorns Have Got to Go
8.plot: Mordecai buys a special cologne to get the attention of Margaret, but it ends up attracting partying unicorns instead.

9.title: Prank Callers
9.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby try to prove that they are good prank callers by pranking the "Master Prank Caller", they are inadvertently transported into the 80's.

10.title: Don
10.plot: Rigby gets jealous of his brother, Don, when he visits the park to stop an audit and is forced to deal with him until he leaves.

11.title: Rigby's Body
11.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby are told that all the snacks in the snack bar are free for employees, they go on a junk-food spree. But, the next day, when Mordecai cops-out, Rigby continues to eat junk-food, and his body, literally, leaves him.

12.title: Mordecai and the Rigbys
12.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby make a fake band, they accidentally enter for a live performance, even though they haven't a clue how to play any instruments.

13.title: Ello Gov'nor
13.plot: After watching a scary movie about a British Taxi, the guys have to help Rigby overcome his fears.

1.title: It's Time
1.plot: When Mordecai turns down Rigby's invite to see a horror movie premiere to go to a chick-flick with Margaret, Rigby gets revenge on him by taking advantage of his shyness to ask Margaret on a date before he can.

2.title: Appreciation Day
2.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby realize that Benson doesn't appreciate them, they change Benson's description of them in the Book of Park Records so they don't seem like bad employees to future bosses.

3.title: Peeps
3.plot: Benson buys a surveillance system to track Mordecai and Rigby's every move when their constant slacking pushes him to the breaking point.

4.title: Dizzy
4.plot: When Maellard asks Pops, his son, to give a speech, Mordecai and Rigby try to help him overcome his stage fright.

5.title: My Mom
5.plot: Mordecai and Rigby are forced to work under Muscle Man and endure his repetitive jokes.

6.title: High Score
6.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to earn respect by increasing their skills on "Broken Bones", an arcade game in the Coffee Shop.

7.title: Rage Against the TV
7.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby make it to the final level in a video-game, their T.V. screen goes black. Now they must find a new T.V. so they can finish the game.

8.title: Party Pete
8.plot: Mordecai and Rigby look for help when their awesome house party turns lame.

9.title: Brain Eraser
9.plot: When Mordecai accidentally sees Pops naked, Rigby tries to find a way to get the image out of his head.

10.title: Benson Be Gone
10.plot: Maellard, feeling Benson is to blame for Mordecai and Rigby's mistakes, demotes him and forces him to work alongside Mordecai and Rigby.

11.title: But I Have a Receipt
11.plot: Mordecai and Rigby expose a bad board game's flaws when the owner refuses to give them a refund.

12.title: This Is My Jam
12.plot: Rigby gets a terrible, terrible song stuck in his head and will go to any lengths to get it out.

13.title: Muscle Woman
13.plot: When Muscleman gets dumped by his girlfriend Starla, he becomes too depressed to do anything, and his work is given to Mordecai and Rigby. They try to get the two back together when the work becomes too much.

14.title: Temp Check
14.plot: Rigby hires a temp to do his work but gets jealous when the temp becomes tight with Mordecai.

15.title: Jinx
15.plot: Rigby must figure out how to unjinx himself without talking.

16.title: See You There
16.plot: Mordecai and Rigby find out that everyone has been invited by Muscle Man to High Five Ghost's birthday party except them. They decide to go anyway.

17.title: Do Me a Solid
17.plot: When Mordecai forces Rigby to go on a double-date with Eileen, Margaret and himself, Rigby accepts, but only if Mordecai owes him ten "solids", or "instant-favors", and plans to use them to sabotage Mordecai's date.

18.title: Grave Sight
18.plot: Mordecai and Rigby plan to host a scary-movie night at the abandoned cemetery in the park so they can raise enough funds to earn a paid-day off.

19.title: Really Real Wrestling
19.plot: Mordecai and Rigby have to take care of Pops, and miss the biggest wrestling match of the year, after they hurt him while wrestling.

20.title: Over the Top
20.plot: Skips accidentally kills Rigby while arm wrestling and fights Death to get him back.

21.title: The Night Owl
21.plot: Mordecai and Rigby team up with Muscle Man and Hi Five Ghost to win a radio contest, but the contest creator wants to turn them against each other.

22.title: A Bunch of Baby Ducks
22.plot: Mordecai and Rigby come across a family of ducks living in a fountain at the park - and take quite a shine to them.

23.title: More Smarter
23.plot: Mordecai begins to make fun of Rigby for not having a high school diploma so Rigby decides to drink a chemical that is supposed to make him smarter.

25.title: First Day
25.plot: The morning after being hired at the park, Mordecai and Rigby both look to obtain Pops' old couch and agree to play a game of rock, paper, scissors to decide who gets it.

26.title: Go Viral
26.plot: Mordecai and Rigby make a bet with Muscleman and High-Five Ghost to see who can get the most views on their internet videos in one week.

27.title: Skunked
27.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby are given the task of picking up road kill, Rigby gets sprayed by a were-skunk. Now, he has to find a cure for the smell before he turns into a skunk, as well.

28.title: Karaoke Video
28.plot: Mordecai and Rigby have to destroy a promotional video tape of them at a Karaoke Club singing and making fun of everyone at the park, when the gang decides to go there.

1.title: Stick Hockey
1.plot: Benson tries to get back Mordecai and Rigby's stick hockey table when he wrongfully gives it away.

2.title: Bet to Be Blonde
2.plot: While playing a video game, Mordecai and Rigby make a bet in which the loser of the game has to wear the hairstyle of their game character. Rigby cheats to win the bet and Mordecai is forced to wear a blonde hairstyle.

3.title: Skips Strikes
3.plot: When the park's bowling team, "The Park Strikers" make it to the championship match in a bowling tournament, Death, the lead member of the rival championship team threatens to reveal Skips' secret if he does not back out.

4.title: Terror Tales of the Park
4.plot: The gang sits around trying to tell the scariest Halloween story.

5.title: Camping Can Be Cool
5.plot: Mordecai and Rigby take Margaret and Eileen to a secret camping spot to show them how great camping is.

6.title: Slam Dunk
6.plot: Mordecai and Rigby challenge Muscleman and High-Five Ghost to a game of basketball for computer rights and so Mordecai can make Margaret a website.

7.title: Cool Bikes
7.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to get Benson to admit they are cool when he bans them from using the cart.

8.title: House Rules
8.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to live on their own when they get tired of Benson's excessive house rules.

9.title: Rap It Up
9.plot: When a skilled rap group know as "CrewCrew" insult Pops and his poems, Mordecai and Rigby join with him when he challenges them to a rap battle.

10.title: Cruisin
10.plot: The guys try to get a girl's phone number in order to win a bet with Margaret and Eileen.

11.title: Under the Hood
11.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to find the man who sprayed graffiti on the bathroom wall when they wrongfully accuse Muscleman and get him fired.

12.title: Weekend at Benson's
12.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby accidentally knock Benson unconscious, they try to make it seem like it was a dream by dropping him off at his apartment, but end up taking him to his neighbors party to help him impress her.

13.title: Fortune Cookie
13.plot: Benson takes the gang to a Chinese Restaurant on a count of his streak of good luck. But when Rigby switches his fortune with Benson's, he gives his bad luck to Benson.

14.title: Think Positive
14.plot: Pops threatens to fire Benson if he does not stop yelling at Mordecai and Rigby.

15.title: Skips vs. Technology
15.plot: Skips tries to learn how to use a computer when Mordecai and Rigby need him to fix Error 220, a virus that as infected the house computer.

16.title: Butt Dial
16.plot: Mordecai accidentally pocket dials Margaret on his cell phone, and he has to erase the embarrassing message he left on her voicemail.

17.title: Eggscellent
17.plot: Mordecai wants to win a hat for Rigby by eating a huge omelet.

18.title: Gut Model
18.plot: Muscle Man wants to be appreciated at the park so he threatens to leave and take a job as a gut model.

19.title: Video Game Wizard
19.plot: Mordecai and Skips decide to work together to win the grand prize in a video game tournament. When Rigby finds out Mordecai chose Skips instead of him, his feelings are hurt.

20.title: Big Winner
20.plot: Mordecai and Rigby have to tell Muscle Man that the million dollar scratcher ticket they gave him for his birthday is a fake without getting killed for it.

21.title: The Best Burger in the World
21.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to outfox Benson using holograms so that they can eat the best burgers in the world.

22.title: Replaced
22.plot: When Benson tries out an ostrich and a possum as replacements for Mordecai and Rigby, they have to fight for their jobs.

23.title: Trash Boat
23.plot: Rigby changes his name and has to change it back when he realizes that he picked the stupidest name ever... "Trash Boat."

24.title: Fists of Justice
24.plot: Mordecai and Rigby have to do Skips' work for the day when he cashes-in a coupon that they gave to him on his birthday.

25.title: Yes Dude Yes
25.plot: Mordecai thinks that Margaret is engaged, and he wants to find a girlfriend as soon as possible to try and get over her.

26.title: Busted Cart
26.plot: Mordecai and Rigby bust up the cart and have to go on a road trip with Benson to the dealership before the warranty expires.

27.title: Dead at Eight
27.plot: Death will spare Muscle Man's life if Mordecai and Rigby babysit his kid and have him asleep before he returns.

28.title: Access Denied
28.plot: Margaret and Eileen invite Mordecai and Rigby to a club, but they are denied entrance because their clothes aren't good enough.

29.title: Trucker Hall of Fame
29.plot: After Muscleman's father dies, Benson asks Mordecai and Rigby to help him get to the Trucker Hall of Fame to spread his Dad's trucker hat ashes.

30.title: Out of Commission
30.plot: When the golf cart owned by the Park goes out of commission, Benson orders Mordecai and Rigby to throw it away. But before throwing it away, the cart comes to life asking them for one more day alive.

31.title: Fancy Restaurant
31.plot: Muscleman has to learn proper mealtime etiquette when he decides to take Starla and her parents to a fancy restaurant to impress them.

32.title: Diary
32.plot: Have you ever read someone's diary? Well has that diary released a giant guardian that wants to destroy you if you don't tell a deep secret? Mordecai, Rigby, and Skips does when Margaret asks if Mordecai and Rigby will water her plants they destroy her diary. But when Skips helps them a little peek from Rigby releases a giant Margaret guardian which they can only stop by like I said a deep secret. Will they reveal a secret or be destroyed by Margaret's diary?

33.title: The Best VHS in the World
33.plot: Mordecai and Rigby have to return an overdue VHS to the store so they won't be banned from renting new movies.

34.title: Prankless
34.plot: Muscle Man vows to never prank again when one of his pranks injures Pops. A rivalry park takes this opportunity to attack the park with pranks of all kinds. The only way the park can be saved is if Muscle Man decides to prank again.

35.title: Death Bear
35.plot: Rigby challenges Mordecai to get a picture inside Death Bear's cage at the abandoned zoo to prove that he isn't afraid of the old folklore.

36.title: Fuzzy Dice
36.plot: The gang tries to win a pair of fuzzy dice for Pops' Birthday. But its not for sale and it is only located in a smelly, greasy arcade known as the "Fun-Fun Zone".

37.title: Sugar Rush
37.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby are given the task of getting donuts for the morning meeting, they buy dangerously double-glazed apple fritters, which Pops eats and becomes high on sugar.

38.title: Muscle Mentor
38.plot: After getting fired by Benson, Rigby goes into the mentor program and Muscle man turns out to be his mentor, things don't go to plan.

39.title: Bad Kiss
39.plot: Mordecai tries to fix his bad kiss with Margaret by using Rigby's time machine.

1.title: Exit 9B
1.plot: When everyone is brainwashed and the park is destroyed, Mordecai and Rigby have to bring everyone back their old selves so they can prevent a highway from being built over the park.

2.title: Starter Pack
2.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to get Muscleman to stop pranking Thomas when they realize that his pranks are getting out of hand.

3.title: Terror Tales of the Park II
3.plot: Mordecai and Rigby are driving to a Halloween party and tell scary stories to pass the time.

4.title: Pie Contest
4.plot: Mordecai and Rigby take over the duty of judging the Park's Pie Contest, but realize that the job isn't all that easy when they find out that they have to pick a winner.

5.title: 150-Piece Kit
5.plot: Benson tries to assemble a 150-piece drum kit to prove that he performed a famous drum solo for a well-known rock band.

6.title: Bald Spot
6.plot: When Muscle Man notices a bald spot on his head, he tries to cover it to keep Starla from seeing it at their date.

7.title: Guy's Night
7.plot: Pops tries to complete the Milk Challenge to prove that he is worthy of becoming one of the guys.

8.title: One Pull Up
8.plot: Rigby must perform a single pull-up to avoid being fired on the grounds of poor personal fitness.

9.title: The Christmas Special
9.plot: Mordecai and Rigby have to destroy a gift for Santa, to save Christmas.

10.title: TGI Tuesday
10.plot: Margaret is transferring to another college, so Mordecai, Rigby and Eileen plan a going-away party at the park's abandoned ballroom, still haunted by its past hosts.

11.title: Firework Run
11.plot: Muscle Man, Mordecai, Rigby, and High five ghost blow up the fourth of July fireworks and are forced to drive to get new ones.

12.title: The Longest Weekend
12.plot: To prove their love for each other, Muscleman and Starla plan to stay away from each other for one weekend.

13.title: Sandwich of Death
13.plot: Mordecai and Rigby buy a potentially deadly sandwich at a restaurant, but when Benson falls ill after he eats it himself, they must set out to find the cure before he dies.

14.title: Ace Balthazar Lives
14.plot: Mordecai and Rigby want to reunite a famous band when they think the lead singer, who was presumably dead, is alive and living in the park.

15.title: Do or Diaper
15.plot: Muscle Man bets Mordecai that if he doesn't kiss Margaret by Friday at midnight, he will have to wear a diaper for a week.

16.title: Quips
16.plot: Skips has to tell is cousin, Quips, to stop telling bad jokes when he comes to visit.

17.title: Caveman
17.plot: While camping out in a cave, Mordecai and Rigby accidentally melt a caveman frozen in a block of ice. When they try to keep him, Benson requires that they make him more civilized.

18.title: That's My Television
18.plot: Mordecai and Rigby help their favorite '80s sitcom star, RGB2, escape from the studio lot and into the mountains to get out of a contract that has trapped him into staying on the show.

19.title: A Bunch of Full Grown Geese
19.plot: When the park becomes invaded by vicious territorial geese, Mordecai and Rigby seek the help of the baby ducks to get rid of them.

20.title: Fool Me Twice
20.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to get on a Japanese Game Show so they can win the grand mystery prize.

21.title: Limousine Lunchtime
21.plot: Mordecai and Rigby accidentally coat the interior of Mr. Maellard's limousine in meatball sub.

22.title: Picking Up Margaret
22.plot: When Mordecai volunteers to drive Margaret to the airport, he tries to convince Benson to let him use his car.

23.title: K.I.L.I.T. Radio
23.plot: Muscleman, Mordecai and Rigby help "Donny G", a famous D.J. take back over the corrupt local radio station so Muscleman can play his song he wrote for Starla on the radio.

24.title: Carter and Briggs
24.plot: Mordecai and Rigby enter a vehicular doughnut contest to win guest spots on their favorite police procedural TV show.

25.title: Skips' Stress
25.plot: Skips faces dire consequences when he passes up a day off to reduce his deadly amount of stress.

26.title: Cool Cubed
26.plot: When Thomas is incapacitated by a dangerously cold slushie flavor, Mordecai and Rigby must enter his brain to prevent the drink from killing him.

27.title: Trailer Trashed
27.plot: A health inspector threatens to shut down the park if sanitary conditions inside Muscle Man's trailer are not improved.

28.title: Meteor Moves
28.plot: Mordecai plans to kiss Margaret at meteor shower to prove to Rigby that he isn't in the "friend zone".

29.title: Family BBQ
29.plot: When Mordecai is invited to a BBQ with Margaret's family, he tries to get her father to give him a handshake.

30.title: The Last Laserdisc Player
30.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to find a laserdisc player so they can see the director's cut of a famous cult classic.

31.title: Country Club
31.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to take back the cart when it is stolen by a rich, snobby country club.

32.title: Blind Trust
32.plot: Blind Trust: Benson has to trust Mordecai and Rigby. / World's Best Boss: The park guys want to give Benson a World's Best Boss mug.

33.title: World's Best Boss
33.plot: The gang wants to give a Benson a "World's Best Boss" mug.

34.title: Last Meal
34.plot: Muscleman gets the guys to take him to fast food joints so he can binge on his favorite foods one last time before going on a couple-diet with Starla.

35.title: Sleep Fighter
35.plot: The gang has to stop Muscleman from fighting in his sleep by finding the source of his nightmares.

36.title: Party Re-Pete
36.plot: The gang tries to save Benson from and evil party company, who kidnap and clone to sell their party-animal counterparts.

37.title: Steak Me Amadeus
37.plot: Mordecai plans to take Margaret out to a fancy restaurant so he can ask her to officially be his girlfriend.

1.title: Laundry Woes
1.plot: Mordecai, still in a state of depression from Margaret's rejection at the Stake Me Amadeus restaurant, ends up finding her sweater in the laundry and plans to give it back to her at her college.

2.title: Silver Dude
2.plot: Mordecai and Rigby decide to create songs and sing them to people in the park so they can raise money to buy a special video game, but they run into a silver street performer who is stealing their songs and dancing to them.

3.title: Benson's Car
3.plot: Mordecai and Rigby have to fix Benson's car when they accidentally throw the T.V. remote into the windshield.

4.title: Every Meat Burritos
4.plot: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscleman, and High-Five Ghost want to eat an Every Meat burrito, but the restaurant won't let them buy any until they have an actual car to use in the drive-through.

5.title: Wall Buddy
5.plot: When Benson tells Mordecai and Rigby to clean their room, Rigby buys a special room-separating system so he doesn't have to clean the mess.

6.title: A Skips in Time
6.plot: When Teenage Skips is accidentally sent into the future while storm-chasing, Mordecai and Rigby have to help him return to the 1700s.

7.title: Survival Skills
7.plot: Mordecai and Rigby have to buy tortillas for Benson's survival seminar, but they get lost in the woods on the way back to the site.

8.title: Terror Tales of the Park III
8.plot: Each of the park guys want to win a bet by telling the scariest story at a Halloween party.

9.title: Tants
9.plot: When Pops gives Tants, the table-pants, to Mordecai an Rigby as a gift, they accidentally ruin them and have to get new ones before their "Tants-Lunch" with Pops the next day.

10.title: Bank Shot
10.plot: Rigby tries to win a dire bet by beating a guy at "Bank Shot", an arcade game that requires skilled and intricate basket ball bank shots.

11.title: Power Tower
11.plot: When Muscle Man is banned from a gym, he tries to win a weight-lifting contest to gain entrance again. But, first he must get his muscles back.

12.title: The Thanksgiving Special
12.plot: Mordecai and Rigby accidentally ruin Thanksgiving and must find a way to save it before their families arrive for dinner.

13.title: The Heart of a Stuntmen
13.plot: Mordecai, Rigby, High-Five Ghost and Muscleman have to get a stuntman license, so they can perform at a little kids birthday, when the original stuntman cops-out at the last minute.

14.title: New Year's Kiss
14.plot: A Rigby that appears to be from the future, tells past-Rigby that he must stop Mordecai from kissing a girl on New Year's Eve.

15.title: Dodge This
15.plot: The gang wants to win a dodge ball tournament, but Mordecai notices that CJ, the girl he kissed accidentally on New Year's Eve, is on a team competing in the tournament.

16.title: Portable Toilet
16.plot: When C.J. dares Mordecai to eat a sandwich inside a portable toilet, Rigby goes with him and ends up getting the door jammed shut with meatball-gravy.

17.title: The Postcard
17.plot: High-Five Ghost gets the help of the guys to remember where he was supposed to reunite with a girl from his past when he receives a "special" postcard from her.

18.title: Rigby in the Sky with Burrito
18.plot: When Rigby receives an invitation to his high-school reunion, he realizes that he hasn't accomplished anything that he claimed he would do. So, with little time he tries to achieve one thing, skydiving while eating a burrito.

19.title: Journey to the Bottom of the Crash Pit
19.plot: When Benson tells the guys that they have to fill up the crash pit, they try to have one last crash caught on tape. But, when they execute the crash, they realize that the video-camera went down with the car and have to get it back.

20.title: Saving Time
20.plot: Benson is mad for Mordecai and Rigby arriving an hour late to the morning schedule. Feeling the scolding was uncalled for, Mordecai and Rigby prank Benson by switching the clocks back 3 hours. Mordecai and Rigby change the park's time-zone.

21.title: Guitar of Rock
21.plot: When Benson breaks Mr. Mallard's special guitar, him, Mordecai and Rigby have to get a new one signed.

22.title: Skips' Story
22.plot: While on break Skips tells Mordecai and Rigby the story and the truth about how he became immortal.

23.title: Return of Mordecai and the Rigbys
23.plot: Mordecai and Rigby, tired of the heat, decide to bring back their band "Mordecai and the Rigbys" so they can enter in a battle of the bands and win an air conditioner.

24.title: Bad Portrait
24.plot: Pops' asks Mordecai and Rigby to pick up a portrait of Benson for his ceremony. But when Rigby ruins it, Mordecai is forced to re-paint it.

25.title: Video 101
25.plot: Mordecai, Rigby and CJ help Eileen with a music video as a final project for her film-making class.

26.title: I Like You Hi
26.plot: Mordecai tries to explain to C.J. that his auto-corrected text "I Like You Hi" was meant to read, "I like Yuji".

27.plot: When Mordecai plans to go on a date with CJ, Death pops up and tells him he has to watch Thomas again.

28.plot: When Rigby is exposed on a surprise television game show for lying, he tries to find the lead host of the show to redeem himself.

29.title: Gold Watch
29.plot: The night before Benson is supposed to be awarded a gold watch for being on-time for work 1000 consecutive days in-a-row, he meets a pair of test pilots at Wing Kingdom and ends up waking up the next morning in the middle of nowhere.

30.title: Catching the Wave
30.plot: Pops wants to learn how to surf so he can become "one" with nature.

31.title: Paint Job
31.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby strip the paint off of the house with the power washer, they have to re-paint the house by the end of the weekend.

32.title: Take the Cake
32.plot: Mordecai and Rigby have to pick up a cake for Mr. Maellard's surprise birthday party.

33.title: Skips in the Saddle
33.plot: When Skips realizes that he is starting to become lonely, he starts to date again, but inadvertently becomes a contestant on a date-game show when Mordecai and Rigby make him an impressive but fake dating profile on a website.

34.plot: When Thomas finds out that Benson is going to fire him, he tries to prove to Benson that he is useful by creating and executing a plan to get back the park's stolen statue.

35.title: Bachelor Party! Zingo!
35.plot: When Quips comes to town for his bachelor party, Skips, the best man, is given the task of getting chicken wings.

36.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby ruin CJ's luxury camping tent, they have to get part-time jobs to raise enough money to buy another one before the camping trip.

37.plot: When Mordecai and CJ realize that they have never been on a romantic date, they schedule one. But, their special gifts that they have secretly planned for the other one coincide and create problems for each other.

1.plot: When Mordecai offers to pick up a mix tape from his parent's house, CJ decides to go with him and meet his parents. But, from past memories, Mordecai worries that his Mom will embarrass him.

2.plot: In high school, Muscle Man wants to show that he is cooler than the new student on campus.

3.title: Daddy Issues
3.plot: CJ joins the mini golf tournament but finds out that her dad signed up. Will she beat him?

4.plot: Mordecai, Rigby, and the gang decide to visit Muscle Man's mother on Halloween. On the way the group tells ghost stories, including one where Mordecai and Rigby die and return to haunt Benson.

5.title: The End of Muscle Man
5.plot: The gang tries to help Muscle Man finish his bucket list.

6.title: Lift with Your Back
6.plot: Rigby tries to prove he can earn a paycheck, but the only job he is qualified for is a strict moving company with a boss that requires him to life boxes with only his back.

7.plot: After Eileen winning a flat-screen tv, Rigby decides to install her new tv to surprise her. The only problem lies within Eileen's roommate who wouldn't let anything new come around her house.

8.plot: After Rigby finds out something unusual about Thomas in the night, he decides to explain his friends about the incident. Meanwhile things starts to turn dangerous when they find out the mysterious truth of Thomas.

9.title: White Elephant Gift Exchange
9.plot: The gang gets back at Muscle Man after he gives them bad gifts.

10.title: Merry Christmas Mordecai
10.plot: After preparing for Eileen's Christmas party, Mordecai finds out that his ex-girlfriend Margaret will be there which leaves him extremely nervous since he doesn't want things to go complicated when he's together with C.J..

11.title: Sad Sax
11.plot: Mordecai tries to get back with CJ.

12.title: Park Managers' Lunch
12.plot: The gang follows Benson to his Park Manager's Lunch hosted by Gene, the rival park manager, thinking that it is all just and elaborate hoax.

14.plot: During an early morning after a late night of partying, Mordecai and Rigby try to take a nap in a patio furniture crate and accidentally get shipped to Australia.

15.title: Married and Broke
15.plot: Muscle Man and Starla participate in a game show to try to win their dream wedding.

16.title: Format Wars II
16.plot: When Mordecai, Rigby and their friends decides to rent a movie on laserdisc, a new prophesy tells them that an all new Format War is heading so they need to be prepared to end the Fomat Wars once and for all.

17.title: Happy Birthday Song Contest
17.plot: Mordecai and Rigby enter into a contest that gives the winner a chance to re-create the "Happy Birthday Song".

18.title: Benson's Suit
18.plot: Benson finds a suit that is designed for battle. But some bad people want it

19.title: I See Turtles
19.plot: Eileen and the gang decide to watch the hatching of the turtles and their descent into the sea.

21.plot: After Mordecai and Rigby play an old video game, they earn a map that leads them to the special prize, "Maury Moto's Golden Game Badge".

22.plot: Mordecai awkwardly attends a party at Margaret's house, hoping to take a piece of cake for C.J.

23.plot: After a horse, with a love of partying, crash-lands on Earth, Mordecai and Rigby learn that he has to pass his U.S. History exam, or else he can never party again.

24.title: Men in Uniform
24.plot: Party Horse: The guys want to help Party Horse pass his U.S. History test. / Men in Uniform: The park guys want to keep the park open for business.

26.title: Brilliant Century Duck Crisis Special
26.plot: The Gang fights a giant robot monster bird.

27.plot: Margaret's double date isn't going so well. Del Hanlon has to pretend he's her boyfriend, but he isn't so good at acting.

28.title: Death Kwon Do-Livery
28.plot: Death Kwon Do-livery: Mordecai and Rigby want to help save Death Kwon Do sensei's life. / Lunch Break: Mordecai and Rigby want to finish a ten-foot sub.

29.title: Lunch Break
29.plot: Mordecai orders a ten foot long sandwich and Benson will fire him and Rigby, if they don't finish the sandwich before the day ends.

30.title: Dumped at the Altar
30.plot: The gang helps Muscle Man get married, but problems arise that involve Mordecai and CJ.

1.title: Dumptown USA
1.plot: Benson is going to fire Mordecai if Rigby can't bring him back from a bizarre land of dudes also known as Dumptown USA.

2.title: The Parkie Awards
2.plot: After Benson doesn't take home the award for Park Manager of the Year, the guys want to make him feel like a winner.

3.title: The Lunch Club
3.plot: Rigby ruins Maellard's fancy lunch, and now he or Benson has to write a letter of resignation.

4.title: Local News Legend
4.plot: Margaret really wants to host a weekly segment on the nightly local news.

5.title: The Dome Experiment Special
5.plot: Benson is determined to prove he was right about the date of the "Dome Experiment".

6.title: Birthday Gift
6.plot: Rigby is on a quest for the best birthday gift for Mordecai instead of usual lame ones.

7.title: Cat Videos
7.plot: Mordecai and Rigby must get Benson to stop watching cat videos.

8.plot: Muscle Man and HFG get struck by lightning after a football match and lose their memory of being friends together. Will they be able to remember?

9.plot: In Regular Show's fifth installment of "Terror Tales," Benson tries to spice up the park's annual Halloween party by renting a wishmaking machine.

10.title: Return of the Party Horse
10.plot: Mordecai and Rigby want to help Party Horse get back together with his girlfriend.

11.title: Sleep Cycle
11.plot: Mortdecai and Rigby mess up their sleeping cycle because of watching a TV marathon and try to fix it.

12.title: Just Friends
12.plot: After Rigby invites Eileen for his big brothers karate presentation, Mordecai gets concerned and worried when hanging out with Margaret.

13.title: Benson's Pig
13.plot: Benson gets a pet pig, and asks Rigby and Mordecai to look after it for him.

14.plot: Rigby goes back to High School to study rocks, but wants to keep it a secret from Eileen.

15.title: Hello China

16.title: Crazy Fake Plan
16.plot: Rigby has to create a massively crazy fake plan in order to surprise Eileen for the first time ever.

17.title: Win That Prize
17.plot: Crazy Fake Plan: Rigby has to create a massively crazy fake plan in order to surprise Eileen for the first time ever. / Win That Prize: Pops wants to go on his favorite game show "Win That Prize," but instead gets deeply involved in the television industry.

18.title: Snow Tubing
18.plot: Rigby tries to get Eileen to go snow tubing.

19.title: Chilli Cook-Off
19.plot: Benson takes place in a chili cook off that needs to be made with ingredients less than $50

20.title: Donut Factory Holiday
20.plot: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscle Man, and High-Five Ghost are watching their favorite "Terrible-Horror" movie "Donut Factory Holiday". They have to get it back to the video store soon, but then they can't get it out of the VCR.

21.title: Gymblonski
21.plot: Rigby has only one more class to get his diploma, P.E but when he finds out the teacher is an old bully he will have figure out how to pass.

22.title: Guys Night 2
22.plot: The bros go on a second adventure before Thomas goes into hiding as an agent

23.plot: Mordecai and Rigby unplug some cables to an old synthesizer, and they have to travel to the planet of Synthos with Skips in order to re-connect them and bring Gary back to life.

24.title: California King
24.plot: Rigby goes to dump to get back his trampoline he regrets throwing away.

25.title: Cube Bros
25.plot: Muscle Man is sick of being used for all the strong jobs at the park. So he decides to work at an office to show people he's smart too.

26.title: Maellard's Package
26.plot: Mordicai and rigby take a job for receiving Mr.Maellard's package,which is very important.

27.title: Rigby Goes to the Prom
27.plot: Rigby Wants to take Elieen to his school prom.

28.title: The Button
28.plot: The Button: The guys have to protect a large red button from being pushed. / Favorite Shirt: Mordecai, Rigby, and High Five Ghost have to somehow get Muscle Man's favorite shirt back on him before he wakes up.

29.title: Favorite Shirt
29.plot: The guys must get Muscle Man's favorite shirt back on him before he awakes.

30.title: Marvolo the Wizard
30.plot: Pops thinks he's mysteriously in medieval times and a wizard named Marvolo.

31.title: Pop's Favorite Planet
31.plot: Marvolo the Wizard: Pops thinks that he's a wizard trapped in medieval times, and he wants to go back home. / Pop's Favorite Planet: When the guys have to sleep outside for the night, Pops wants to see his favorite planet.

32.title: Pam I Am
32.plot: Benson try to win over a dome employee named Pam by sneaking her hot wings.

33.title: Lame Lockdown
33.plot: The head scientist puts Mordecai and Rigby on a 24-hour lock down inside the Dome, but they want to sneak out and see one of their favorite bands.

34.title: VIP Members Only
34.plot: The guys hope to be VIPs at Cheeser's.

35.title: Deez Keys
35.plot: Mordicai and Rigby have to sneak into the dome laboratory to get Benson's keys back.

36.title: Rigby's Graduation Day Special
36.plot: In a half hour special, Rigby has to give a speech at his high school graduation. The speech will be broadcast live on a TV show called "Inspire America," and Rigby wants to make it memorable.
